INSERT INTO `event_faqs` VALUES (1,'How can a school register to become a member of Pune Sahodaya School Complex?','The school should be affiliated with the Central Board of Secondary Education and must have a valid CBSE Affiliation Number while registering. Visit the Members section on the homepage, select Register, fill in all required details, and click Submit.',10,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(2,'Will the school automatically become a member after submitting the registration form?','No. Membership is confirmed after the registration form is completed, membership fees are paid through Demand Draft or NEFT, the PSSC Committee reviews and approves the registration, and a unique PSSC Code is issued for future correspondence.',20,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(3,'Can members update content or post photos in the photo gallery?','Members need to send the content or photographs via email to sahodayapune24@gmail.com. The Committee reserves the right to approve and publish any content or photographs on the website.',30,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(4,'What are the advantages of joining PSSC?','Benefits include sharing ideas and best practices, common timetables and question papers for Classes IX, X, and XII, Principal and Teacher Workshops, CBSE-sponsored workshops, literary and cultural festivals, and sports festivals.',40,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(5,'What is the procedure for a member school to share an event organized by their school?','Send a circular with complete details of the proposed event to the PSSC Chairman and email it to sahodayapune24@gmail.com. Approved events are published under Events - Sahodaya Events along with the e-invite.',50,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(6,'Who can attend the workshops and training programs organized by PSSC?','Principals, Vice-Principals, Coordinators, Teachers, Counselors, and Students from member schools can participate in workshops, seminars, competitions, and training programs organized by PSSC.',60,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(7,'How will schools receive information about upcoming events and workshops?','Official circulars, workshop details, event notifications, and competition updates are shared through the PSSC website, official email communication, and WhatsApp groups for member schools.',70,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(8,'Can non-member schools participate in PSSC events?','Participation in most PSSC activities is primarily reserved for member schools. Selected workshops or conferences may allow non-member participation based on availability and committee approval.',80,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(9,'Is there a membership fee for joining PSSC?','Yes. Schools are required to pay the prescribed membership fee through approved payment methods such as NEFT or Demand Draft. Fee details are communicated during the registration process.',90,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(10,'How can schools contact the PSSC Committee for support or clarification?','Schools may contact the committee through the official email ID sahodayapune24@gmail.com. Queries related to membership, workshops, competitions, events, and website updates can be addressed through email communication.',100,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(11,'Can member schools host PSSC events or workshops?','Yes. Member schools interested in hosting workshops, competitions, cultural events, or meetings may send a proposal to the PSSC Committee for review and approval.',110,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(12,'Are certificates provided for workshops and competitions?','Yes. Participation certificates, appreciation certificates, and merit certificates are provided for eligible workshops, training sessions, and competitions organized by PSSC.',120,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(13,'How can schools update their contact details or Principal information?','Schools should send an official request from the registered school email ID to the PSSC email address with updated details and supporting information.',130,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(14,'What types of competitions are organized by PSSC?','PSSC organizes literary competitions, cultural events, sports tournaments, STEM and robotics competitions, quiz competitions, art and craft activities, and entrepreneurship programs.',140,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(15,'Does PSSC organize CBSE-related orientation programs?','Yes. PSSC regularly conducts orientation sessions and capacity-building programs aligned with Central Board of Secondary Education guidelines for teachers and school leaders.',150,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(16,'Can schools suggest new activities or initiatives to PSSC?','Yes. Member schools are encouraged to share innovative ideas, collaborative programs, and suggestions with the PSSC Committee for consideration and implementation.',160,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(17,'How are event registrations completed?','Registration links and participation details are shared through official circulars. Schools are requested to complete registration before the deadline mentioned in the event circular.',170,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(18,'What happens if a school changes its management or Principal?','The school must officially inform the PSSC Committee regarding changes in management, Principal, or authorized coordinators to ensure smooth communication and record updates.',180,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(19,'Are networking opportunities available through PSSC?','Yes. PSSC provides a collaborative platform where educators and school leaders can exchange ideas, share best practices, and build professional connections.',190,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42'),(20,'Does PSSC support student leadership and innovation initiatives?','Yes. PSSC encourages student participation in leadership programs, innovation projects, entrepreneurship activities, and collaborative learning initiatives across member schools.',200,'active','2026-05-25 12:21:42','2026-05-25 12:21:42');
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `event_faqs` ENABLE KEYS */;
